aa(lp231
VBut again, when it comes to the decisions which are
p232
aVimpacting us the most, perhaps, the most important
p233
aVdecisions that are being made about war and so forth,
p234
aVagain we can't just make a Freedom of Information request.
p235
aVIt's really difficult. So we're still having to rely on
p236
aVillegitimate ways of getting information, through leaks.
p237
aVSo when the Guardian did this investigation about
p238
aVthe Afghan War, you know, they can't walk into
p239
aVthe Department of Defense and ask for all the information.
p240
aVYou know, they're just not going to get it.
p241
aVSo this came from leaks of tens of thousands of dispatches
p242
aVthat were written by American soldiers
p243
aVabout the Afghan War, and leaked,
p244
aVand then they're able to do this investigation.
