aa(lp308
VSo what is the solution? It is, I believe, to embody
p309
aVwithin the rule of law rights to information.
p310
aVAt the moment our rights are incredibly weak.
p311
aVIn a lot of countries, we have Official Secrets Acts,
p312
aVincluding in Britain here. We have an Official Secrets Act
p313
aVwith no public interest test. So that means it's a crime,
p314
aVpeople are punished, quite severely in a lot of cases,
p315
aVfor publishing or giving away official information.
p316
aVNow wouldn't it be amazing, and really, this is what I want
p317
aVall of you to think about, if we had an Official Disclosure Act
p318
aVwhere officials were punished if they were found
p319
aVto have suppressed or hidden information
p320
aVthat was in the public interest?
p321
aVSo that \u2014 yes. Yes! My power pose. (Applause) (Laughs)
p322
aVI would like us to work towards that.
p323
